        output='# Q1 2026 Revenue Disaggregation Analysis\n\n## Complete Revenue Disaggregation Tables\n\n### Table 1: Revenue by Products and Services (Q1 2026)\n\n| Line Item | Three Months Ended March 31, 2026 | Three Months Ended March 31, 2025 |\n|---|---|---|\n| Products | $380 | $352 |\n| Services | $4,314 | $3,715 |\n| **Total revenues** | **$4,694** | **$4,067** |\n\n### Table 2: Revenue by Type and Segment (Q1 2026)\n\n| Line Item | Three Months Ended March 31, 2026 | Three Months Ended March 31, 2025 |\n|---|---|---|\n| Launch Services | $330 | $566 |\n| Launch & Development | $289 | $299 |\n| **Space** | **$619** | **$865** |\n| Consumer | $2,148 | $1,492 |\n| Enterprise & Government (1) | $1,109 | $983 |\n| **Connectivity** | **$3,257** | **$2,475** |\n| Advertising | $343 | $443 |\n| AI Solutions & Infrastructure | $475 | $284 |\n| **AI** | **$818** | **$727** |\n| **Total revenues** | **$4,694** | **$4,067** |\n\n*(1) Enterprise & Government revenue includes revenue from Starlink Mobile service offerings.*\n\n---\n\n## Answers to Your Questions\n\n### (1) Is the $380 million Products revenue included within the $2,148 million Consumer revenue, or is it separate?\n\nThe $380 million Products revenue is **not separate from** the segment table — it is **embedded within** the $3,257 million Connectivity segment total. The document explicitly states:\n\n> *"All of products revenue is attributable to the Connectivity segment."*\n\nThis means the two tables are **different views (cross-tabulations) of the same $4,694 million total revenue**, not additive layers. The $380 million in Products revenue sits *inside* the $3,257 million Connectivity segment figure. The Products revenue primarily represents Starlink Kit hardware sales, which would be distributed across the Consumer and Enterprise & Government sub-categories within Connectivity.\n\n### (2) Services vs. Products Breakdown for the Connectivity Segment\n\nSince all $380 million of Products revenue is attributable to Connectivity, and total Connectivity revenue is $3,257 million:\n\n| Connectivity Revenue Type | Amount (Q1 2026) |\n|---|---|\n| Products (Starlink Kits, terminals) | $380 million |\n| Services (broadband subscriptions, mobile, enterprise, government) | $2,877 million |\n| **Total Connectivity** | **$3,257 million** |\n\n### (3) Key Relationships Across the Two Tables\n\nThe two disaggregation views reconcile as follows:\n\n| Segment (Table 2) | Revenue | Products (Table 1) | Services (Table 1) |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| Space | $619 | $0 | $619 |\n| Connectivity | $3,257 | $380 | $2,877 |\n| AI | $818 | $0 | $818 |\n| **Total** | **$4,694** | **$380** | **$4,314** |\n\nThe Space and AI segments generate **entirely Services revenue** (Launch Services, Launch & Development, Advertising, AI Solutions & Infrastructure), while the Connectivity segment is the **sole source of Products revenue** — consistent with it being the segment that sells physical Starlink Kits and terminals alongside its subscription services.',
